msgstr "`firstname = ?1 and status = ?2` será mapeado para `{'firstname': ?1, 'status': ?2}`"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/mongodb-panache.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`amount > ?1 and firstname != ?2` will be mapped to `{'amount': {'$gt': ?1}, 'firstname': {'$ne': ?2}}`"
msgstr "`amount > ?1 and firstname != ?2` será mapeado para `{'amount': {'$gt': ?1}, 'firstname': {'$ne': ?2}}`"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/mongodb-panache.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`lastname like ?1` will be mapped to `{'lastname': {'$regex': ?1}}`. Be careful that this will be link:https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/query/regex/#op._S_regex[MongoDB regex] support and not SQL like pattern."
msgstr "`lastname like ?1` será mapeado para `{'lastname': {'$regex': ?1}}`. Tenha cuidado, pois isso utilizará o suporte a link:https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/query/regex/#op._S_regex[regex do MongoDB] e não o padrão SQL like."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/mongodb-panache.adoc
